    {
      "id": 100618701,
      "date": "2026-03-30",
      "name": "Aerobic Ramps",
      "type": "WORKOUT",
      "sport_type": "Ride",
      "planned_tss": 44,
      "duration_hours": 0.88,
      "duration_formatted": "53m",
      "workout_summary": "3m @106W | 1m @121W | 1m @131W | 1m @164W | 1m @221W | 2m @101W | 4m @179W | 2m @102W | 5m @144W | 2m @122W | 4\u00d75m @144W / 2m rec",
      "description": "Not every session needs to involve high-intensity efforts. Today's session is a low-intensity workout focussing on your aerobic fitness.\n\nOne of the most important aspects of cycling is your aerobic fitness. This allows you to preserve vital glycogen stores and power up the day's final climb.\n\nWarmup\n- 90^ The warmup gradually increases in power. 130^ By increasing your aerobic fitness, you will improve your ability to recover from the long climbs. 160^ Now we ramp up the power each minute to continue the warmup.<!> 3m ramp 44.9-60%\n\n- 1m 60%\n- 1m 64.9%\n- 31^ Just the 1min effort above threshold now.<!> 1m 81%\n- 1m 109%\n- 80^ 4min just under threshold will complete your warmup.<!> 2m 50%\n- 80^ This is the level of power you can expect to target on a long climb.<!> 4m 88.4%\n- 60^ The main set today consists of 5 x 5min aerobic efforts.<!> 2m 50.4%\n\nWarmup\n- 106^ As the power increases aim to hold the same cadence. 235^ The last minute should see an increase in your breathing rate.<!> 5m ramp 61.4-80.4%\n\n- 47^ For the recovery we keep some pressure on the pedals.<!> 2m 60.4%\n\nWarmup\n- 240^ This is the kind of workout you can perform several times during the week.<!> 5m ramp 61.4-80.4%\n\n- 55^ Remember, it's fine to complete some low intensity work.<!> 2m 65.4%\n\nWarmup\n- 236^ How does the last minute feel? 281^ Still comfortable?<!> 5m ramp 61.4-80.4%\n\n- 68^ Just 2 intervals to go.<!> 2m 65.4%\n\nWarmup\n- 151^ Are you holding the same cadence as the earlier intervals? 171^ A decreased cadence indicates fatigue is accumulating.<!> 5m ramp 61.4-80.4%\n\n- 58^ Last effort now.<!> 2m 65.4%\n\nWarmup\n- 143^ This is a good session to maintain your aerobic fitness.<!> 5m ramp 61.4-80.4%\n\nCooldown\n- 30^ Now for a nice cool down.<!> 5m ramp 75.4-50.4%"
    },
